You can use [assertj][1]-fluent assertions. It has lot of capabilities to write assertions in more human readable - user friendly manner. 

In your case, it would be

     String x = &quot;foo bar&quot;;
     assertThat(x).contains(&quot;foo&quot;);

It is not only for the strings, it can be used to assert lists, collections etc.. in a friendlier way 

